description:
Estrada Media Serials is a collection of short stories about various characters from different creators.

The first story comes from the mind of Nick Burns, about a wrestler known as Timo Bolamba.

The second story is based upon a futuristic Utopia where murder runs rampant by Dave Reeves.

The third story is from Jake Estrada, about a genetically altered dog.

While the final story is about a serial killer from the deranged mind of Frankie Rodriguez so beware.

The book is an intense 32 pages of action and macabre. Cover is drawn by Nino Mesarina (The Unbelievable Laundry Detergent Man, fame).

Black and white, with color cover.
